arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)

	--Vigo Move Action
	Hydra.QActorMoveToLocationDynamicSpeed(ID_VIGO_EVENT, LOC_VIGO_MOVE, "NPC_WALK_FAST", true)
	Hydra.QActorFadeAndDelete(ID_VIGO_EVENT, 1)
	
	-- Make the weather MORE intense
	Hydra.WeatherIntensityOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.4, 9999)
	
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)

	--Cleanse Relic
	Hydra.QActorPlayEffectGroup(ID_RECEP_CURSE_03, FX_HOLY_BLESS)
	Hydra.QActorWait(ID_RECEP_CURSE_03, 2)
	Hydra.WaitForQEmpty(ID_RECEP_CURSE_03)
	Hydra.ActorDisable(ID_RECEP_CURSE_03)
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_RECEP_DUMMY_03)
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_HOLY_CARRYABLE_01)
	
	-- Make the weather MORE intense
	Hydra.WeatherIntensityOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.7, 9999)

end

function Start(idActorNPC, sConversation, idActorPlayer)
	
	--Enable Carryable 
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_CURSED_CARRYABLE_01)
	
	-- Start the Stormy Look
	Hydra.WeatherOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, WEATHER_OVERRIDE)
	Hydra.WeatherIntensityOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.2, 9999)
	
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)
	
	--Cleanse Relic
	Hydra.QActorPlayEffectGroup(ID_RECEP_CURSE_01, FX_HOLY_BLESS)
	Hydra.QActorWait(ID_RECEP_CURSE_01, 2)
	Hydra.WaitForQEmpty(ID_RECEP_CURSE_01)
	Hydra.ActorDisable(ID_RECEP_CURSE_01)
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_RECEP_DUMMY_01) 
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_CURSED_CARRYABLE_02)
	
	-- Make the weather MORE intense
	Hydra.WeatherIntensityOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.5, 9999)
	
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)
	
	--Cleanse Relic
	Hydra.QActorPlayEffectGroup(ID_RECEP_CURSE_02, FX_HOLY_BLESS)
	Hydra.QActorWait(ID_RECEP_CURSE_02, 2)
	Hydra.WaitForQEmpty(ID_RECEP_CURSE_02)
	Hydra.ActorDisable(ID_RECEP_CURSE_02)
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_RECEP_DUMMY_02)
	Hydra.ActorEnable(ID_CURSED_CARRYABLE_03)
	
	
	-- Make the weather MORE intense
	Hydra.WeatherIntensityOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.7, 9999)
	
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorReceptacle)
	-- Clear the Weather Override
	Hydra.ClearWeatherOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY)
	
	-- Set this to match the standard intensity, and give it a lifetime.
	-- In 5 seconds, ALL overrides are lifted from the Frac_Glacier subzone / Sanctuary_eastern_continent world.
	Hydra.WeatherIntensityOverride(WORLD_SANCTUARY, 0.5, 5)
end

szOnStartupScript:
-- This is the stormy weather used when progressing through the quest - unrelated to the carryable visual override.
WEATHER_OVERRIDE = Hydra.ReferenceWeather("weather_FracturedPeaks_AlabasterMonastery_storm")
WORLD_SANCTUARY = Hydra.ReferenceWorld("Sanctuary_Eastern_Continent")
